THEORY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  4 PILLARS OF OOP:
  1. Encapsulation   : Binding data and methods together; hide internal state.
  2. Inheritance     : Child class acquires properties of parent class.
  3. Polymorphism    : One interface, multiple implementations.
  4. Abstraction     : Hide implementation, show only essential features.

  INHERITANCE TYPES:
  -> Single       : A extends B
  -> Multilevel   : A extends B, B extends C
  -> Hierarchical : B extends A, C extends A

  Method Overriding: Child class redefines parent's method (same signature).
  Dynamic Method Dispatch: JVM decides which overridden method to call at runtime.

